  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, a portion of which has already been restituted. Due to the lack of criminal history and the cooperative gestures regarding restitution, a significant prison sentence is not appropriate. While embezzlement is a breach of fiduciary duty, the interruption by a spectator is irrelevant to the legal determination of the sentence. A sentence of 6 months serves as a sufficient deterrent consistent with the nature of the crime.",
